<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-01 01:05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nurses Strike at Mass. Hospital  </HEADLINE>
By JEFF DONN, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   WORCESTER, Mass. (AP) -- The first strike by registered nurses in
Massachusetts in 14 years came at an awkward time for officials at
St. Vincent Hospital, who long ago had picked today to move into
the hospital's new, $215 million building.
</P>
<P>
   But as angry nurses donned placards and began an
around-the-clock picket outside the new and old facilities Friday,
hospital officials declared the move would still be made.
</P>
<P>
   Officials planned to transfer most hospital units, staff and
patients to the new building, about one mile away.
</P>
<P>
   Contract talks broke down Wednesday and the strike began early
Friday as some workers left work in uniforms to head to the picket
line.
</P>
<P>
   ''They're looking at the numbers, they're looking at the money,
and we're sick of it!'' said Judy Read, a 10-year nurse at the
hospital. Her picket sign said: ''Corporate Greed Is to Blame.''
</P>
<P>
   The nurses, who have been in contract negotiations for over two
years, reached agreement on 3.5 percent annual raises. But they
disagreed over the hospital's insistence to reserve the right to
require overtime when needed.
</P>
<P>
   Hospital managers say the mandatory overtime provision ensures
they can staff the hospital in any contingency. The nurses say
managers are really trying to avoid hiring additional staff that is
needed.
</P>
<P>
   The hospital kept operating Friday with 64 non-striking regulars
and 62 replacement nurses. State health regulators, who were
monitoring, said those nurses were caring for 172 patients at the
329-bed hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The hospital had a pre-strike nursing staff of 535. It wasn't
immediately clear how many were striking, but the strike was
authorized by a better than 2-to-1 margin.
</P>
<P>
   The hospital's chief executive officer, Robert Maher Jr., has
said managers could hold out in a strike for months and run the
hospital safely.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   Massachusetts Nursing Association site:
http://www.massnurses.org/
</P>
<P>
   Saint Vincent Healthcare System:
http://www.tenethealth.com/SaintVincent
</P>
</TEXT>
