<HEADLINE> Time To Set the Clock Ahead Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Set the clocks ahead tonight.
</P>
<P>
   Daylight-saving time returns at 2 a.m. Sunday, providing an
extra hour of evening sunshine until Oct. 29 for most of the United
States.
</P>
<P>
   It's also a good time to replace batteries in smoke alarms,
safety advocates urge.
