<HEADLINE> Report: Burns To Buy JFK Jr. Loft  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Actor Edward Burns has negotiated a deal to buy
John F. Kennedy Jr.'s loft apartment in the trendy TriBeCa
neighborhood, the Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
   Burns, who has appeared in such films as ''Saving Private Ryan''
and ''She's The One,'' negotiated a bid less than the reported
minimum $2.5 million asking price, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
   The 2,400-square-foot loft, in a nondescript former commercial
building, has been on the market via sealed bids by Sotheby's
International Realty. Kennedy paid $700,000 for the loft in 1994.
</P>
