<HEADLINE> Time To Set the Clock Ahead Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Daylight-saving time is back.
</P>
<P>
   Officially, clocks for most of the country were changing at 2
a.m. Sunday. Folks who failed to spring forward were an hour late
for work, church or other activities.
</P>
<P>
   Daylight-saving time brings an extra hour of evening sunshine
for outdoor activities until Oct. 29.
</P>
<P>
   This also is a good time to replace batteries in smoke alarms,
safety advocates say
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
