<HEADLINE> Actor Ed Burns Might Buy JFK's Pad  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The late John F. Kennedy Jr.'s loft apartment
could soon be in the hands of actor Edward Burns.
</P>
<P>
   Burns, 32, has negotiated a deal to buy the posh penthouse in
New York's trendy Tribeca neighborhood for less than the reported
minimum $2.5 million asking price, both the Daily News and the New
York Post reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy bought the 2,400-square-foot loft in a nondescript
former commercial building for $700,000 in 1994. It has been on the
market via sealed bids by Sotheby's International Realty.
</P>
<P>
   Burns, who has appeared in such films as ''Saving Private Ryan''
and ''She's The One,'' still needs approval from the property's
co-op board.
</P>
<P>
   A spokeswoman for Sotheby's realty wouldn't comment. Mara
Buxbaum, Burns' publicist, said the actor had no comment.
</P>
<P>
   Kennedy, his wife, Carolyn, and her sister were killed in July
when the plane Kennedy was piloting crashed off Martha's Vineyard.
</P>
</TEXT>
