<HEADLINE> Kenya Bus Plunge Kills 11  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) -- A crowded bus plunged into a river in
western Kenya Saturday, killing at least 11 passengers.
</P>
<P>
   The accident comes the same week as Kenya's deadliest-ever bus
accident, a fiery head-on collision between two buses in which 74
passengers burned alive.
</P>
<P>
   The latest accident occurred when a bus hit a pothole and
careened into the Gianchera river, traffic patrol officer Thomas
Atipo said. Sixty-six seriously injured survivors were
hospitalized, Atipo said.
</P>
<P>
   The accident happened 150 miles northwest of Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
   Although long-distance buses in Kenya generally are licensed to
carry only 62 passengers, most carry many more -- often, double the
official limit.
</P>
</TEXT>
