<HEADLINE> Sunday's TV News Show Lineup  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lineup for the Sunday TV news shows:
</P>
<P>
   ABC's ''This Week'' -- Topics: The Elian Gonzalez case, gun
safety and the New York Senate race. Guests: Rep. Charles Rangel,
D-N.Y.; Sen. Robert Torricelli, D-N.J.; Manny Diaz, attorney for
Elian's Miami relatives; Smith &AMP; Wesson President and CEO Ed
Schultz and Rep. Rick Lazio, R-N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   CBS' ''Face the Nation'' -- Topics: Elian Gonzalez, White House
agenda and Minnesota Gov. Jesse Ventura. Guests: Linda
Osberg-Braun, lawyer for Elian's relatives in Miami; Reps. Lincoln
Diaz-Balart, R-Fla., and Jose Serrano, D-N.Y.; White House chief of
staff John Podesta and Ventura.
</P>
<P>
   NBC's ''Meet the Press'' -- Topics: Fund-raising investigations
and Campaign 2000. Guests: Charles LaBella, former chief of the
Justice Department's Campaign Finance Task Force, and Sen. John
McCain, R-Ariz.
</P>
<P>
   CNN's ''Late Edition'' -- Topics: The New York Senate race,
presidential politics, Elian Gonzalez and congressional
investigations of the White House. Guests: Peggy Noonan, author and
former Reagan speechwriter; former New York Gov. Mario Cuomo, Rep.
Dan Burton, R-Ind., chairman, House Government Reform Committee;
Greg Craig, attorney for Juan Miguel Gonzalez, Elian's father; and
Spencer Eig, attorney for Elian's relatives in Miami.
</P>
<P>
   ''Fox News Sunday'' -- Topics: Elian Gonzalez and President
Clinton's accusation that Republicans are shameless. Guests: Sen.
Connie Mack, R-Fla.; Reps. Robert Menendez, D-N.J., and Steve
Largent, R-Okla.; Sen. Mitch McConnell, R-Ky.
</P>
</TEXT>
