<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-01 15:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Accused of Locking Mom in Closet  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- A man is accused of locking his mother
in a closet in her own home for three days and beating her with a
belt because she wouldn't give him money.
</P>
<P>
   David Parks, 35, also threatened to cut off his mother's toes,
gave her a garbage bag to use as a toilet and fed her nothing but
stale popcorn, police said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   L. Michaeleen Parks, 59, was treated at a hospital for cuts and
bruises and released, Sgt. Bruce Elrod said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the ordeal began Monday when Michaeleen Parks
refused to give her son money for his rent, saying he would have to
wait until she was paid at the end of the week. Parks also was
upset that his mother had put her husband in a nursing home,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, Parks realized his mother needed medical help, but
rather than attracting attention by going to a hospital he took her
to a beauty salon where a friend works, police said. The friend
took Parks to a drugstore, allowing Michaeleen Parks to call
police.
</P>
<P>
   Parks was charged with first-degree kidnapping and willful
injury. Bail was set at $100,000.
</P>
</TEXT>
