Protesters Oppose Returning Elian
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   MIAMI, Fla. (AP) -- About 100 Cuban-Americans protesting the Immigration and
Naturalization Service order to return 6-year-old Elian Gonzalez boy to his
father in Cuba gathered outside the boy's Miami relatives' home today. A
nonprofit group called the Cuban Information Committee ran a full-page ad in The
Miami Herald touting reasons why Elian should stay in America. The leader of the
Miami-based anti-Castro group Democracy Movement said it is poised to react if
the government attempts to take Elian. The INS has threatened to revoke the
boy's residency status, but twice last week pushed back a deadline for the
relatives to agree, now set for 9 a.m. Tuesday.
