<HEADLINE> Detroit Apartment Fire Kills 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- Two people jumped to their deaths from the eighth
floor of a burning apartment building Saturday as people below
attempted to catch them in a blanket. A 2-year-old girl also died,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Dozens of residents fled the 12-story building after fire broke
out in an apartment on the eighth floor, said Andrew Angelucci, a
senior fire chief. Smoke and heat quickly swept upward, he said.
</P>
<P>
   An 8-year-old girl and another person were in critical condition
at Henry Ford Hospital, said hospital spokesman Dave Olejarz. Three
other people were also hospitalized and an off-duty police officer
was treated at the scene.
</P>
<P>
   The names of the dead were not immediately released.
</P>
<P>
   ''We tried to catch them in a blanket,'' Jaquelyn Porter told
WXYZ-TV.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the fire was under investigation, Angelucci said.
</P>
</TEXT>
