<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-01 23:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hornets 90, Bulls 87  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Elden Campbell scored 25 points and Eddie Jones
added 23 as the Charlotte Hornets won their sixth straight, 90-87
over the Chicago Bulls on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Anthony Mason added 15 points, nine rebounds and seven assists
for the Hornets, who led 81-71 with 5:26 left.
</P>
<P>
   Hersey Hawkins' 3-pointer following a Charlotte turnover pulled
the Bulls to 87-84 with 52 seconds remaining. Elton Brand made one
of two free throws with 20 seconds left and followed with a dunk as
Chicago closed to 88-87 with five seconds to go.
</P>
<P>
   But Jones made two free throws, and Chris Carr missed a 3-point
shot from halfcourt.
</P>
<P>
   Brand had 24 points and eight rebounds for the Bulls, who have
lost four straight, and Ron Artest scored 20.
</P>
<P>
   Eight quick points from Brand helped Chicago take a 17-7 lead,
but Charlotte went ahead for the first time on its final possession
of the quarter, 21-20 on two Jones free throws.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulls came back as Artest scored 11 points during 19-8 run
and regained the lead 39-29 at with just over three minutes left.
Charlotte then closed the half with a 10-4 spurt to chop Chicago's
lead to 43-39.
</P>
<P>
   Jones' 3-pointer closed Charlotte to 52-50 with 7:24 left in the
third. Following a Bulls' turnover, David Wesley inbounded to a
streaking Jones,. who in turn passed to Campbell for a breakaway
layup, tying the game at 52.
</P>
<P>
   Another run, this one 19-8 by Charlotte, ended the third and
gave the Hornets a 71-60 lead.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Mason entered averaging 20.4 points, 11 rebounds and 8.6
assists in his previous five games. ... The Hornets are 14-4 when
Mason leads them in assists. ... Derrick Coleman had an inflamed
left knee and did not dress. ... The Hornets have won six straight
times against the Bulls. ... Chicago's Fred Hoiberg sprained his
left ankle midway through the third quarter and did not return.
</P>
</TEXT>
