<HEADLINE> Report: Redskins Pursuing QB George  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Washington Redskins are prepared to offer
free-agent quarterback Jeff George a multiyear contract, The
Washington Post reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The Post, quoting unidentified sources close to the team, said
George, who spent last season with Minnesota, would be a backup to
former Vikings quarterback Brad Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota coach Dennis Green has said he would like to re-sign
George to a one-year deal.
</P>
<P>
   Leigh Steinberg, George's agent, did not immediately return a
call to The Associated Press on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   George, 32, was 9-3 as a starter last season, leading Minnesota
into the playoffs, where the Vikings lost to St. Louis.
</P>
<P>
   The Vikings pursued Dan Marino as a replacement for George, but
the Miami star retired rather than sign with Minnesota.
</P>
