<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-01 23:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Burn 1, Mutiny 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS (AP) -- Jason Kreis became the fourth player in MLS
history to score 50 goals, connecting on a header in the 69th
minute to lead the Dallas Burn over the Tampa Bay Mutiny 1-0 on a
soggy Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Kreis, last year's league MVP, scored on a corner kick from Chad
Deering for his second goal of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Before 11,491, Dallas goalkeeper Matt Jordan, who set the MLS
shutout record with 11 last year, stopped five shots for his first
of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa Bay (2-1) played without MLS leading scorer Raul Diaz
Arce, who joined El Salvador for a World Cup qualifier against
Guatemala on Sunday. Dallas (2-1) was without midfielder Jorge
Rodriguez, who was also playing for El Salvador.
</P>
<P>
   The Mutiny played with 10 players in the final minutes after
second-half substitute Daniel Hernandez was ejected.
</P>
<P>
   Diaz Arce, Miami's Roy Lassiter and Giovanni Savarese, formerly
of New England, are the only other MLS players to score 50 goals.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
